<ref name="epistemology">Donald Rutherford, ''The Cambridge Companion to Early Modern Philosophy''（Cambridge University Press, 2006）, p. 1: "epistemology assumes a new significance in the early modern period as philosophers strive to define the conditions and limits of human knowledge."</ref>

