<ref name="existentialists">Religious thinkers were among those influenced by Kierkegaard. Christian existentialists include [[Gabriel_Marcel|Gabriel Marcel]], [[Nicholas_Berdyaev|Nicholas Berdyaev]], [[Miguel_de_Unamuno|Miguel de Unamuno]], and [[Karl_Jaspers|Karl Jaspers]]（although he preferred to speak of his "philosophical faith"）. The Jewish philosophers [[Martin_Buber|Martin Buber]] and [[Lev_Shestov|Lev Shestov]] have also been associated with existentialism.</ref>

