<ref name="justification">{{cite book|editor=T. Honderich, ed|chapter=The ethics of philosophical practice|author=Anthony Quinton|title=牛津哲学指南（The Oxford Companion to Philosophy）|publisher=牛津大学出版社|page=666|isbn=978-0-19-866132-0|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=sI4YAAAAIAAJ|quote=哲学是一种理性的批判性思维，或多或少对自然世界进行[[:wikt:系统化|系统化]]（形而上学或存在论），信仰辩护（认识论或知识论），和人生引导（伦理学或价值理论）。上述列表中的三个元素都有一个非哲学的副本，区别在于哲学那理性批判的程序和其系统性。每个人对自己所生活的自然世界都有自己的基本观念。形而上学替代那些未加辩论的假设归纳出这么一个作为一个整体理性地组织世界的概念。每个人都在某种情境下会在对他们在做的事并没有任何理论认识的情况下质疑自己或他人的信仰并伴随着或多或少的成功。认识论寻求通过辩论来明确正确信仰形成的规则。每个人通过把行为引导到期望的或有价值的目标来支配自己的行为。伦理学或道德哲学在其最包容的意义下旨在阐明在理性的系统化情境下包含的规则或原则。|date=1995|access-date=2014-05-02|archive-date=2020-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924160731/https://books.google.com/books?id=sI4YAAAAIAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>

<ref name="kierkegaard">{{cite book |author=Matustik, Martin J. |title=Kierkegaard in Post/Modernity |publisher=Indiana University Press |isbn=978-0-253-20967-2|date=1995}}</ref>

<ref name="metaphysical">Kenny, ''A New History of Western Philosophy'', vol. 3, p. 211: "The period between Descartes and Hegel was the great age of metaphysical system-building."</ref>

<ref name=Misere>{{cite book|author=卡尔·马克思|title=Misère de la philosophie. Réponse à la philosophie de la misère de M.Proudhon哲学的贫困|date=1847}}</ref>

<ref name="naturalistic">Copleston, ''ibid.'': "The bulk of Renaissance thinkers, scholars and scientists were, of course, Christians ... but none the less the classical revival ... helped to bring to the fore a conception of autonomous man or an idea of the development of the human personality, which, though generally Christian, was more 'naturalistic' and less ascetic than the mediaeval conception."</ref>

