<ref name="tufts2">[[西塞罗|西塞罗]], ''{{le|图斯库卢姆辩论|Tusculan Disputations}}'', 5.3.8–9 = {{le|赫拉克利德斯·彭提烏斯|Heraclides Ponticus}} fr. 88 Wehrli, [[第欧根尼·拉尔修|第欧根尼·拉尔修]]1.12, 8.8, [[楊布里科斯|楊布里科斯]]''VP'' 58. Burkert attempted to discredit this ancient tradition, but it has been defended by C.J. De Vogel, ''Pythagoras and Early Pythagoreanism''（1966）, pp. 97–102, and C. Riedweg, ''Pythagoras: His Life, Teaching, And Influence''（2005）, p. 92.</ref>

<ref name=Webster>{{cite web |url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/philosophy |title=Philosophy |work=Mirriam-Webster在线字典 |access-date=2014-05-02 |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129140543/https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/philosophy |dead-url=no }}</ref>

<ref name="Webster's New World Dictionary">哲學的定義為：「1.智慧或知識的源頭、熱愛，或對此之追尋；2.對行為、思考、知識與宇宙的本質等原則、理論或邏輯的分析。」{{cite book|title=Webster's新世界字典|edition=Second College}}</ref>
}}

